Receptionist Appointments Page Flow
===================================

File:
- src/pages/receptionist/Appointments.jsx

Purpose:
- Let receptionist users book, view, reschedule, and manage appointments.
- Keep appointment data linked to real patient records and doctor availability.

Core Data Sources:
- Patients: loaded from patient storage (`getPatients` in `src/utils/patientStorage.js`)
- Doctors: loaded from localStorage key `clinicone_doctors`
- Appointments: loaded/saved in localStorage key `clinicone_appointments`

Main Workflow
-------------
1) Open appointments page
- Existing appointments are loaded from localStorage.
- If none exist, seed appointments are created.

2) Search and filter appointments
- Search by patient name, doctor name, appointment ID, or phone.
- Date filter: `All`, `Today`, `Upcoming`, `Past`
- Status filter: `All`, `Scheduled`, `Completed`, `Cancelled`, `No Show`
- Doctor filter: filter by doctor ID/name selection.

3) Book a new appointment
- Click `Book Appointment`.
- Choose booking mode:
  - `Existing Patient`: select from current patients.
  - `+ New Patient`: create patient inline, save to patient storage, then use that patient for booking.
- Select doctor:
  - Default doctor list shows only `Available` doctors.
  - Optional toggle to show unavailable doctors.
- Select date and time slot.
- Select appointment type and optional notes.
- On submit, validations run:
  - required fields must be filled.
  - selected doctor must be `Available`.
  - no conflict for same doctor/date/time.
  - no conflict for same patient/date/time.
- Successful booking is saved with status `Scheduled`.

4) Manage existing appointments
- `View`: opens a read-only details modal.
- `Reschedule`: opens edit modal for patient/doctor/date/slot/type/status/notes.
- `Cancel`: sets status to `Cancelled`.
- `Complete`: sets status to `Completed` (shown for scheduled appointments).

Validation Rules
----------------
- New inline patient:
  - valid first/last name
  - valid DOB
  - phone required
  - email must include `@`
- Appointment:
  - patient, doctor, date, time required
  - doctor status must allow scheduling
  - conflict prevention against existing non-cancelled appointments

Status Mapping in UI
--------------------
- `Completed` -> green (`confirmed`)
- `Cancelled` -> red (`cancelled`)
- other statuses (`Scheduled`, `No Show`) -> amber (`pending`)

Notes
-----
- This page is receptionist-focused and uses localStorage persistence.
- It is independent of backend APIs in the current implementation.
